    "If the output of the model contained words for cues or roles that were not in the given sample, and no other word with a Levenshtein distance of 1 was found in the sample, we ignored those words.",
    "Then, if the output was empty, we mapped the output to the marker #UNK# (unknown).",
    "Resolving ambiguities.",
    "A word may occur more than once in a sample.",
    "When a model outputs such a word as a cue or a role, it is unclear to which occurrence of the word in the sample it should be attributed."
